definitions.definition: To occur after an event or time ; to exist later on in time.
To assign an effective date to a document or action later than the actual date .
examples: to postdate a contract, that is, to date it later than the time when it was in fact made

definitions.definition: To affix a date to after the event.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To occur after an event or time ; to exist later on in time.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To assign an effective date to a document or action later than the actual date .
( transitive ) To affix a date to after the event.
